{"text":"Since your blood sugar (FP) is a bit below the target (89 mg/dL), you'll want to reduce the insulin to avoid going too low.

Adjustment calculation for low blood sugar:
- Target: 100 mg/dL
- Current: 89 mg/dL
- Difference: 11 mg/dL
- ISF: 12 mg/dL/U

Adjustment Units = 11 mg/dL / 12 mg/dL/U  0.917 units

Recommended insulin dose: 4.7 units
